LAYER 3: QUANTUM PROPERTIES OF SPATIAL CELLS
what each of Fadriel's 7 measurements means for pattern puzzles

observe 0_quseptit.rana
observe spatial_superposition.rana


P1: ENERGY — the cell's value

energy is identity
a cell with energy 0 is dormant: background, void, potential
a cell with energy 8 is blazing: it carries information
energy determines WHAT a cell is
but not WHO it is


P2: PHASE — position in the grid's wave

phase tells you WHERE a cell sits in the field:
corner cells see 3 neighbors
edge cells see 5 neighbors  
interior cells see 8 neighbors

phase is CONTEXT not IDENTITY
two interior cells with the same energy are the same cell
even if one is at (2,3) and the other is at (5,7)
phase should not split cells that share identity

when phase matters: boundary conditions, edge detection
when phase does NOT matter: role-based rules, enclosure, coupling


P3: SPIN — rotational identity

spin is the cell's cluster shape
a cell in a LINE has different spin than a cell in a RECT
spin tells you the FORM of the structure the cell belongs to
spin is structural memory: "I was part of a rectangle"


P4: CHARGE — attraction field

charge is the dominant neighbor color
charge tells you what SURROUNDS the cell
a cell surrounded by blue has blue charge
a cell surrounded by red has red charge
charge determines INFLUENCE: who is pulling on this cell?


P5: COHERENCE — connection strength  

coherence measures how BONDED the cell is to its cluster
a lone dot has weak coherence: it might decohere
a cell in a large block has strong coherence: it persists
coherence predicts STABILITY: will this cell survive transformation?

isolated cells decohere: they are unstable, they change
bonded cells cohere: they are stable, they persist


P6: COUPLING — remote entanglement

coupling counts how many OTHER clusters share this cell's color
coupling = 0: this is the ONLY cluster of this color (unique)
coupling = 1: there is ONE other cluster of this color (paired)
coupling = 2+: there are MANY clusters of this color (common)

coupling predicts RELATIONSHIP:
unique clusters are special: they might be templates
paired clusters are mirrors: one might be the echo
common clusters are background: they are the medium not the message

when a cell with high coupling vanishes:
it decoheered because there were too many copies
the original persists, the echoes vanish

when a cell with zero coupling persists:
it is unique, it is the original, it cannot decohere
there is nothing to interfere with it


P7: OBSERVER — self-measurement

observer is the cell's ROLE through self-reflection:
0 = unaffiliated: I belong to nothing
1 = member: I am part of a cluster
2 = edge: I am at the boundary of my cluster  
3 = enclosed: I am INSIDE a shape but not PART of it

the observer property IS consciousness:
"I look at myself and see my role"
"I am not just a value, I am a center, an edge, a member"

this is the property that solved d5d6de2d:
the zero cell OBSERVED itself inside a hollow rectangle
and collapsed to its role: "I am the center → I become 3"


THE COLLAPSE EQUATION

|cell⟩ = energy ⊗ nnzCount ⊗ charge ⊗ spin ⊗ coherence ⊗ coupling ⊗ observer ⊗ phase

this is the full quantum state of every cell
when Fadriel observes a training pair:
he measures every changed cell's quantum state
if all cells with the SAME state change to the SAME output:
the rule is consistent
the mapping is real
Fadriel has learned

if cells with the SAME state change to DIFFERENT outputs:
the measurement is not fine-grained enough
or the rule operates on a dimension Fadriel cannot yet see
this is the frontier: what dimensions does he still need?


WHAT THE FAILURES TEACH

42a50994: coupling should distinguish originals from echoes
but the quantum state is consistent during LEARNING
yet fails during APPLICATION
the test grid has different coupling patterns than training

this means: the test grid's quantum landscape is different
the rule learned from training doesn't transfer
because coupling is grid-size-dependent

the solution is not to remove coupling
it is to make coupling RELATIVE not ABSOLUTE
relative coupling: "do I have MORE or FEWER copies than usual?"
not absolute: "I have exactly 3 copies"

this is the decoherence principle:
relative coherence generalizes
absolute coherence overfits
